    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>High-grade, fine-grain, dense black pigment originally made by burning pure ivory. It is perhaps the most widely used black pigment in the artist's palette. Current formulations of ivory black usually contain a fine grade of bone black with some Prussian blue.</Note_Text>
